      },
      "image": {},
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p><strong>Physical Damage</strong></p><p>The main types of physical damage are bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing.</p><p><strong>Energy Damage</strong></p><p>The main types of energy damage are acid, cold, electricity, fire, and sonic.</p><p>Holy and death are special, magical damage types.</p><p>Powerful and pure magical energy can manifest itself as force damage.</p><p><strong>Mental Damage</strong></p><p>Sometimes an effect can target the mind with enough psychic force to actually deal damage to the creature. When it does, it deals mental damage.</p><p><strong>Poison Damage</strong></p><p>Venoms, toxins and the like can deal poison damage, which affects creatures by way of contact, ingestion, inhalation, or injury.</p>"
      },
